snippet: The bottom line is that on Wednesday morning, Mitt Romney’s chances of becoming president were a little higher than they were 24 hours ago, quite a bit higher than they were 24 days ago.
abstract: FiveThirtyEight blog; Mitt Romney's victory at the Iowa caucuses, though slight, puts him in a better position than any other Republican contender, and in a far better position than he found himself only a month ago.
lead_paragraph: The bottom line is that on Wednesday morning, Mitt Romney’s chances of becoming president were a little higher than they were 24 hours ago, quite a bit higher than they were 24 days ago.

headline.main: Romney’s Ugly Win May Be a Charm
